      <div class="post-28 page type-page status-publish hentry" id="post-28">
       <h2 class="entry-title">
        Home
       </h2>
       <div class="entry-content">
        <h1>
         <strong>
          BIG OLE NEEDS BIG REPAIRS!
         </strong>
        </h1>
        <p>
         Big Ole, the famous statue of a jolly Viking in Alexandria, MN, is 50 years old, and needs attention, which will cost $24,500. A family of birds is nesting in his shoulder. His cape is made of two pieces that are splitting apart, and the wind could separate them completely. The fiberglass is peeling off and turning to dust. The paint is peeling in many places. His most recent paint colors were not the best, giving him a solid cream color face and beard. The Runestone Museum owns Big Ole and must maintain him. The $24,500 is a very large price for us to pay. Can you help out a little? We will keep a graphic on this page, showing the progress we are making toward restoring Big Ole, with your donation.Please donate to the
         <a href="http://www.runestonemuseum.org/giftshop/help-repair-big-ole/" title="Help Repair Big Ole!">
          Big Ole Repair Fund
         </a>
         . Or, you can send a check, or bring one to our gift shop.
        </p>
        <h3>
         <span style="color: #800000;">
          <strong>
           Your donation is tax-deductible!
          </strong>
         </span>
        </h3>
        <h2>
         Follow the progress on the sword below:
        </h2>
        <table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
         <tbody>
          <tr>
           <td valign="top" width="212">
            <a href="https://www.runestonemuseum.org/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/Big-Ole.png">
             <img alt="Big Ole" class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-1557" height="378" src="https://www.runestonemuseum.org/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/Big-Ole-139x300.png" width="175"/>
            </a>
           </td>
           <td valign="top" width="411">
            <a href="https://www.runestonemuseum.org/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/Sword-Red-progress.png">
             <img alt="Sword- Red progress" class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-1559" height="379" src="https://www.runestonemuseum.org/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/Sword-Red-progress-35x300.png" width="44"/>
            </a>
            When the red color reaches the top of the sword, our goal of raising $24,500 in Viking Loot will be reached, and we can pay for the repairs to Big Ole!
           </td>
          </tr>
         </tbody>
        </table>
        <p>
         <a href="https://www.runestonemuseum.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/runes.jpg">
          <img alt="runes" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1226" height="19" src="https://www.runestonemuseum.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/runes.jpg" width="868"/>
         </a>
        </p>
        <h1>
         <script type="mce-text/javascript">
          // &lt;![CDATA[

         <span style="color: #0000ff;">
          <strong>
           Welcome!
          </strong>
         </span>
        </h1>
        <h1>
         <span style="color: #0000ff;">
          <strong>
           We have the Runestone!
          </strong>
         </span>
        </h1>
        <p>
         Welcome to the Runestone Museum, located in downtown Alexandria, Minnesota. We invite you to stop by and tour historic Fort Alexandria, take your picture with the countrys biggest viking, and see the world famous Kensington Runestone.
        </p>
        <p>
         <a href="https://www.runestonemuseum.org/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/runestone.jpg">
          <img alt="" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-84" height="306" src="https://www.runestonemuseum.org/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/runestone.jpg" title="runestone" width="200"/>
         </a>
         For a while you will live in the past, so walk a little slower, talk a little slower, and enjoy the exhibit on Norse history, the Native American exhibit, the Minnesota wildlife display, the display of early pioneer life, and the hands-on childrens area.
        </p>
        <p>
         Enter Fort Alexandria and visit several authentic log buildings, an 1880 country school house, and view the forty-foot viking ship, the Snorri. Experience the changing of the seasons in the display of tools and farm equipment used by an earlier generation. For a preview see the
         <a href="https://www.runestonemuseum.org/exhibits/" title="Exhibits">
          Exhibits
         </a>
         page.
        </p>
        <p>
        </p>
        <p>
         Would you like to help support the work of the Runestone Museum? If the answer is YES, click on the
         <a href="https://www.runestonemuseum.org/membership/" title="Support Us">
          Support Us
         </a>
         page for more information.
        </p>
        <p>
         <a href="https://www.runestonemuseum.org/sponsors/" title="Sponsors">
          <span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">
           <strong>
            Click here to see who our 2015 Sponsors are!
           </strong>
          </span>
         </a>
        </p>
        <p>
        </p>
        <table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
         <tbody>
          <tr>
           <td valign="top" width="319">
            <p align="left">
             Kids, enjoy the Scavenger Hunt! Pick up a clipboard from the Immigrant Trunk.
            </p>
           </td>
           <td valign="top" width="319">
            <a href="https://www.runestonemuseum.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/clipboard.jpg">
             <img alt="clipboard" class="size-thumbnail wp-image-1115 alignleft" height="150" src="https://www.runestonemuseum.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/clipboard-150x150.jpg" width="150"/>
            </a>
           </td>
          </tr>
         </tbody>
        </table>
        <p>
         <span style="color: #ff0000;">
          <b>
           Bring your cell phone!
          </b>
         </span>
         <br/>
         We have the OnCell system, which plays audio descriptions of many of our exhibits.
        </p>
        <p>
         <img alt="" class="alignleft" height="137" src="data:image/png;base64," width="72"/>
        </p>
        <p>
         The OnCell project is made possible in part by the voters of Minnesota through grants from the Lake Region Arts Council, thanks to a legislative appropriation from the Arts and Cultural Heritage fund.
        </p>
        <p>
        </p>
        <p>
        </p>
        <p>
         <a href="https://www.runestonemuseum.org/gift-shop/" title="Gift Shop">
          <img alt="gift shop2" class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-1127" height="150" src="https://www.runestonemuseum.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/gift-shop2-150x150.jpg" width="150"/>
         </a>
         The Runestone Gift Shop features Minnesota, Alexandria and Big Ole souvenirs. Viking and runestone information, books, t-shirts, viking helmets and swords, and unique gifts, which many of them are by local artists, authors, and craftspeople. Visit the
         <a href="https://www.runestonemuseum.org/gift-shop/" title="Gift Shop">
          Gift Shop
         </a>
         to purchase online.
        </p>

        </p>
